      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BORROWED TIMES (8) finished fifth on debut then ran a much improved race last start to claim his maiden win by 6 lengths (22.25) at Maitland. Jumps from the same draw this time. Was a winner at his only start from this draw. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. GREENGROCER TOM (7) is progressing well scoring last time out (17.47) at this track and bringing up his 2nd career win. Goes very well here at the trip finding the frame in each of three starts. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. One of main contenders. PONY TAIL (5) has been in sparkling form, last time breaking from this same box to win a Grade 5 at this track (17.26) and making it four straight wins. Can measure up again. SLICK SILAS (2) was out of the money at this circuit last start but can make amends.",
